04/01/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish authorities detained a total of 55 illegal immigrants in the border provinces of Edirne and Hatay, local media reported on Saturday (January 3rd).
One group was trying to enter Greece, while another was targeting Syria.
Police will deport the Pakistani, Iraqi and Syrian nationals once courts complete legal proceedings.
(Anadolu news agency, NTV, Zaman - 03/01/09)
